cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY

This paper focuses on the application of deep learning for radio resource allocation in multi-cell networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper extensively discusses deep neural networks and their architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of genetic algorithms, which is a topic related to optimization and algorithms, indicating that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
